name: Celeste Williams
message: Rep. Womack, if you truly knew this district, you’d be able to tell them why you ignored the Fayetteville Board of Health's plea for more COVID testing in early July. Or why NWA topped the New York Times’s running list of highest COVID growth regions for weeks on end this summer.

name: Celeste Williams
message: In his most recent term alone, Rep. Womack has voted to loosen regulations on mercury and other air toxins, methane and carbon pollution, offshore exploratory drilling, and the protection of marine life. He's earned a lifetime score of 4% from the League of Conservation voters.

name: Celeste Williams
message: Would love to know where you’re getting your stats from, Rep. Womack. The CRS report delivered to you and your colleagues assessing Trump’s tax bill told you that the TCJA reduced the poverty gap by approximately half the effect of other needs-tested programs. We need tax reform.

name: Celeste Williams
message: Rep. Steve Womack blames you for making more with $600 unemployment insurance than you do at your job. Arkansans deserve a living wage. I’m curious to know why he voted against the Raise the Wage Act.

name: Celeste Williams
message: Best practices, Rep. Womack, includes proper mask wearing. https://t.co/zrpqPUsBYU

name: Celeste Williams
message: Rep. Steve Womack refers to me as an “armchair quarterback” during this pandemic. How insulting. I’m a nurse. I’ve been on the front lines this entire time as Rep. Steve Womack has voted against stimulus checks for Arkansans and done nothing to protect us.

name: Celeste Williams
message: Trump threw away the pandemic playbook, and Rep. Womack has stood by him every step of the way. Do not let him escape responsibility at at the ballot box. We must hold every leader complicit in this tragedy accountable.

name: Celeste Williams
message: In fiscal year 2019, the year Steve Womack was Chair of the House Budget Committee, the budget deficit totaled $984 billion — $205 billion more than the shortfall recorded in 2018. He is hardly an authority on debt management.

name: Celeste Williams
message: Steve Womack says this is the most important election of our lifetime. He’s right. If we re-elect him, he will slash Social Security, Medicare, and Medicaid — leading to poverty and social unrest for years to come. We must take a stand this November.

message: "Anyone else who recklessly squandered lives and money in this way would be suffering legal consequences. Our leaders have largely claimed immunity for their actions. But this election gives us the power to render judgment."

name: Celeste Williams
message: The NIH have played a key role in vaccine development but have been excluded from much crucial government decision making. And the FDA has been shamefully politicized, appearing to respond to pressure from the administration rather than scientific evidence."

name: Celeste Williams
message: " The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, which was the world’s leading disease response organization, has been eviscerated and has suffered dramatic testing and policy failures."

name: Celeste Williams
message: "The response of our nation’s leaders has been consistently inadequate. The federal government has largely abandoned disease control to the states."

name: Celeste Williams
message: The United States came into this crisis with enormous advantages. Along with tremendous manufacturing capacity, we have a biomedical research system that is the envy of the world... Yet our leaders have largely chosen to ignore and even denigrate experts."

name: Celeste Williams
message: "The government has appropriately invested heavily in vaccine development, but its rhetoric has politicized the development process and led to growing public distrust."

name: Celeste Williams
message: The United States instituted quarantine and isolation measures late and inconsistently, often without any effort to enforce them, after the disease had spread substantially in many communities. "

name: Celeste Williams
message: "...a lack of emphasis on developing capacity has meant that U.S. test results are often long delayed, rendering the results useless for disease control."

name: Celeste Williams
message: "We have failed at almost every step. We had ample warning, but when the disease first arrived, we were incapable of testing effectively and couldn’t provide even the most basic personal protective equipment to health care workers and the general public."

name: Celeste Williams
message: "In general, not only have many democracies done better than the United States, but they have also outperformed us by orders of magnitude."

name: Celeste Williams
message: "Covid-19 is an overwhelming challenge, and many factors contribute to its severity. But the one we can control is how we behave. And in the United States we have consistently behaved poorly."

name: Celeste Williams
message: "Here in the United States, our leaders have failed that test. They have taken a crisis and turned it into a tragedy."

name: Celeste Williams
message: Covid-19 has created a crisis throughout the world. This crisis has produced a test of leadership. With no good options to combat a novel pathogen, countries were forced to make hard choices about how to respond."

name: Celeste Williams
